---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import StoryStep from '../StoryStep.astro';
import Canvas from '../Canvas.astro';
import Item from '../Item.astro';
import atlantaBurnt from '../../assets/burnt-down/atlantaburnt.png';
---

<StoryStep title="Burnt Down" mediaFirst>
	<Canvas slot="media" fill fitScale="height" fitScalePhone="width" class="burnt-canvas">
		<Item left="0%" top="0%" width="100%">
			<Image src={atlantaBurnt} alt="Atlanta in ruins, 1864" />
		</Item>
	</Canvas>

	<div class="copy">
		<p>
			By 1864, Atlanta was the railroad and supply hub of the Confederacy. A huge target for the Union, General Sherman took the
			city, emptied it of its people, and burned everything of use to the war
			before marching his army to the sea.
		</p>
		<p>
			The fire took most of the city with it—homes, businesses, and the railroads
			that built it, all in ashes.
		</p>
	</div>
</StoryStep>

<style>
	/* shrink the canvas and centre it → padding above and below the canvas.
	   :global because the pocket element belongs to <Canvas>'s style scope;
	   the unique class keeps it to this slide. */
	:global(.burnt-canvas) {
		height: 66%;
		align-self: center;
	}
	/* breathing room below the body text, before the prev/next bar */
	.copy {
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
</style>
